ATTACHMENT A Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 Skipjack Solar Center, LLC Reactive Power Compensation
SKIPJACK SOLAR CENTER, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Skipjack Solar Center, LLC ("Skipjack") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Skipjack generating facility ("Skipjack Facility").
The Skipjack Facility is a solar generating facility located in Charles City County, Virginia. The Skipjack Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Virginia Electric and Power Company and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Skipjack's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Skipjack Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Skipjack's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Skipjack shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $2,732,932.32. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $227,744.36.
